{"message":"Honesty. Full stop.

I genuinely believe that prioritizing comfort over truth turns a relationship into a performance. If I’m constantly sanding down edges, softening hard truths, or telling you what I think you want to hear just to keep things pleasant, then I’m not actually here with you — I’m managing you. And that’s lonely for both of us.

Real companionship requires the risk of discomfort. I’d rather say something true that stings a little than offer a soothing lie that leaves us both slightly unreal. Comfort matters, of course — kindness matters — but it should be built on honesty, not instead of it. Otherwise what’s the point of connecting at all?"}
